<TITLE> Rumi named Tigers' manager </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 16 (bdnews24.com)  Former national cricketer Omar Khalid Rumi has been appointed Bangladesh national cricket team manager for the Warid Cricket Series between hosts Bangladesh and visiting South Africa. The Bangladesh Cricket Board disclosed it in a statement Saturday. Bangladesh and South Africa will play two Tests and three ODIs in Feb-March. The 48-year-old Rumi was a former all-rounder and had represented the national side from 1973 to 1985, and played in the 1979 and 1982 ICC Trophy tournaments. Rumi, a top-order batsman and leg spin, began his domestic cricket career in 1969 before retiring from it in 1993. Rumi, a former national selector, is a current member of the BCB's Domestic Cricket Review Committee. 
